\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid8593187 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 If I could ask you when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 1896.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Whereabouts was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Over at Horton, Woodley Arton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Is this a village or is it -?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh no, I was out on the wilds as you might say. I had the farthest for to go to school. Two mile to walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Had you any other houses round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Well the farmer as I worked for thirty years. I wa
s born in a cottage about 300 yards away as the crow flies. And I went to live in the old house where, as he bought afterwards. When the \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 estate was sold up. The farmers, they worked hard before that see. One of his brothers lived in that house 
and he was born there. And his uncle lived there before that. And then there was another brother down at his mill farm. Well he down at mill farm he was more boss than the one that lived in this old thatched house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 What was your father's job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Farm labourer. Like meself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 It was the farmer's cottage that you had then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 That's only a cottage on the farm. That's the last cottage in the lane. In them days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 How large was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 What the cottage? Well this was two up and two down. Then w
here I went to live, after the war, before I got married, cos I was married in 1915, and I went to this other old farm house in 1918. And then we stopped in there until 1948 when I shifted over to Old Sodbury on account of the wife cos if she wanted anyth
i
ng extra we had to come to Sodbury for to get it. And that was no unthankful office especially on a bike, a push bike. When you get out on Sodbury Common you know which way the wind is blowing. And I used to come across there of an evening if we wanted su
mmat, extra. Sometimes I have had to stand on the pedals and I had to get off and walk when the wind was so rough all against me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Yes, bad isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh it is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Had you a garden at your first cottage where you were brought up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh that was 
two gardens as you might say. One was one side of the road a three cornered piece and the other was adjoining the cottage. That wasn't what,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13060952\charrsid7686223  \{blank\}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223  oh I suppose all together it wouldn't be half an acre. Then when I went to live in this old thatched farm h
ouse well that was half an acre of garden to say nothing about the lawn and all that. And twelve month before we left over there I had the first prize for the garden. And he was twelve perch long. And wasn't the full length of the garden as was dug up see
. And that was 96 rows of 'taters, two feet apart. And sometimes when the onions and all that during the war, well I didn't plant, the biggest part were onions and the rest of em were shallots. And sell 'em. For to get the extra shilling.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Did your father grow vegetables as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 What sort of things did he grow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Some of them all sorts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 I see. Had you any fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 In this other, in this other old thatched house, it used to be a farmhouse in years gone by. Well I put it down to 300 year old but }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14749910\charrsid7686223 I}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223  was a long way out as it was more than 1600.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Yes, very old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 That was six rooms on him, three up and three down. Terrible great beams they were anyone wouldn't realize it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 And when we went into it, I had to put some thatch on first because the estate lot see let it go. And I put some on there because the}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13060952\charrsid7686223  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
thatcher that used to do all the houses thatching he was away at timber cutting. When he came home well the farmer had it thatched all over see then. He done it once aft
erwards. While I was there. When I left there, the fellow that took my job see, both of them was a little bit touched, I am sorry to say, and the old doctor said afterwards when the master, he came and see the missus, Mrs Stinchcombe, \{BLANK\}
 imagine that, and \{ILLEGIBLE\} they come from the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13060952\charrsid7686223 beans. I}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 t was a darned great big whitened passage and \{BLANK\}
 just inside the front door and then there was the baking oven adjoining that see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 It must have been a very large house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh yes it was. Fact of the matter when I went into it first there was a \{BLANK\}
 and cheese press there and a beating stone. What become of it I couldn't say. I forgot all about that. And the cheese room was up over, or supposed to be the cheese room. When the thatchers came first I 
said we better cut that there by root off hadn't I he said "No" he said "he is holding up the house". Da}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13060952\charrsid7686223 rn it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
, it was as big as my body I was afraid it might part. And up in this cheese room when the children got big see well we wanted the room. And I aske
d the farmer about having it done and he said "No" well Mrs. Come over to the Council about it well they said if the farmer doesn't want the land well he must do it himself and so I had it done and then they got over in, I know what was like inside. Oh it
 
was all blooming joy ..... And I got and cleaned it all out and I can tell you I was in a blooming mess. Black as soot. And sweat as well. And then had it done out and 'twas a darn big room, in fact we could put three double beds in there if it was wanted
. Well three boys did have that and the girls did have the room on top of the stairs. And to the Mrs. Had the other big rooms, and had one of the girls in there see, if we wanted them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 It was big then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh it was and it was nice and cool in the sum
mer and warm in the winter. Far better than these is today. This is all ... Well fact of the matter, on top of the stairs when they made this other room, cause before hand you see you had to step up high for step over into this old cheese room. Well they 
m
ade a place on the landing or the stairs see into the cheese room. You wouldn't hardly have believed it. It was like a stake and heather hedge. Where it was twisted in a lump and that was black thorn and I suppose they used to go down you see it was about
 as big as my thumb, that was hard as iron for to cut see and that was all plaster, with clay see put on with your hands and that was as hard as iron.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 How many rooms were there on the ground floor then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 You had a kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh yes a big large kitchen. It was as big as the hall and this together. And wider too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 A big fireplace was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
Oh ah. An old fashioned fireplace. Well years ago before I went into it I can remember it see, in me school days, cause years ago the vicar a
s was at Horton in the wintertime he did have a prayer meeting see at each, one night a week at each farm. Well all on us, I don't say all on us, but a lot of us did always go to these prayer meetings. And when that vicar retired from Horton went into Bat
h
, there's a cousin of mine was at service long with him at Horton, course that was right on top of the hill then large house and when he went there and came out to Yate and opened the Y.M.C.A. down at Yate and when her got back his house was all (whispers
) burnt? And my cousin only had just what she stood up in. And I went for to see her afterwards, she were engaged for to be married at Christmas and I went to see her afterwards out at \{BLANK\} up in Forest o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16591344\charrsid7686223 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223  Dean and when I got there, she, poor thing, was gone into convalescence, never seem her I biked it on me own. I was in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place
}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Gloucester{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}eight o'clock
{\*\xmlclose} in the morning. Push biking when I got back, come back, and got back to Wedminster, called into a pub there and got talking, tell them where I'd been, oh the
y said, you needn't went all round there if you'd have gone down to Claycliffs you could have gone over on the ferry over to Newnham and Newnham's on the bottom and \{ILLEGIBLE\} on top of the hill.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Too late wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Yes, it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Had your father hens and pigs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
I had some poultry. Fowls. Hatch our own chickens. We had a big lawn see and I could hatch em out up there see on the lawn or have the chicken on the lawn. He was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591344\charrsid7686223 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 arn big lawn it was. And we had, and there was a walnut tree and a
 pear tree there on the lawn. In the garden, well when I went into it first, well it was more like an orchard than it was a garden cause the old farmer well he'd grafted all the trees see he'd grafted all the trees that was in the garden well I got any am
ount on }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591344\charrsid7686223 \lquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
em out because it were no good, especially in the middle of the garden cause it takes all the goodness out of the soil cos they were so big, some on em were as big round as my body. And kept the best on em, best of the apples and on several occasio
ns see well I didn't make enough cider for to last us the best part of the season, having a little drop at a time. Cause we always had plenty of beer or cider see at work. At all the farms. All the farmers was the same. Always had plenty of beer or cider.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Would your mother made cider and beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
Yes. And the Mrs. did, well fact of the matter before well I married her she'd been making butter and cheese for John Russell down here, it was then, well that's where the international is today. He bought 
the cheese that she had made down at Yate. Down at Mr Flowered then down {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Broad Lane{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 it is today. And I had the front room covered in cheese that she made. And since, I was on to the daughter about it to see if she could remember and she said yes she can. C
os I had to go down to clinic you see every so often and that to have my toe nails cut was two miles, cos I've had 'em stepped on me, horses carts and one blessing it got better now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 And she did always come up and pick me up and take me down and bring me back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 I see. How many brothers and sisters had you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Well I was the odd one out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 How many were there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Well, let's see. Three, five. Yes. Five altogether? Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Were you the eldest, or youngest, or in the middle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 The youngest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 It must have been a bit squashed in the house
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 How did you manage, were there girls in one bedroom and boys in the other?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Well we \{ILLEGIBLE\} managed some how or other. Some on em used to sleep downstairs see. On the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16591344\charrsid7686223 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 ouch. Or on the sofa in them days. There was no couches, not like this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Had you a front room and a kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh no. Only a kitchen. No front rooms there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 How big was the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Bit bigger than this one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Quite a size.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Yes. And th
e pantry place, well when, before I got married, after I left school, cos there was a school mistress in my school days and then afterwards she retired and a school master come then. Well then he got up some evening classes well there was about a dozen on
 us used to go to these evening classes. Then we got on carpentry. Well I got and made a safe then. Bout that long, 3', 3 x 2. And this 'ere cream mesh wire, so as to put your vegetables and that in. Or else it was all \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 open rest of it was. And dust and all that would get into it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Had your parents any water in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
No, no water. We had to fetch our own water well you had to go along to the farm for to get the water. And as for washing and swilling down well we had a little pond dow
n the road. And up where I finished off, we had no water there, we had to fetch it from the farm. We had a pond there see, where we could have water from for washing and swilling down cos that was land drainage water come into that pond. And after, about 
twelve months after I left there, well they had the water and the electric put in. Cos my eldest son up and brought it from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Dunkirk{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 on the top road, through Hawkesbury and down through the commons through Horton and finished up at Colonel Walkers and come o
n the mains. It was all candle and oil lamps then and we had an oil stove, a double burner see with the oven on top. We could do our cooking then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 How did your parents make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Well }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591344\charrsid7686223 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 t}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591344\charrsid7686223  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 was a struggle. Ah. Cause when I got married it was f
ifteen shillings a week and me house. One me Mrs. I bought her that there sewing machine before we was married cause her sister had one see and she was a tailoress and so her sister showed her how to use that one well she could make her own clothes and ch
ildren}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16591344\charrsid7686223 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 s clothes and all on it. Had some old trousers come in \{ILEGIBLE\}
 and make they up for the boys. And the girls the same, ladies clothes, cut it to pieces and make it up for them. Oh she was a good hand on that job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Did your mother make your own clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Where did they come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
Well we did buy them see. Well fact of the matter I was out at work see in me school days to pick up a shilling or two and fact of the matter on one or two occasions when I was carrying straw for th
e thatcher, or the farmer, well he gave me five bob see for carrying straw for him, well I came over to Mr. Martins where Jack? Is today, and bought a suit of clothes for five bob.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 You managed that way did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh yes. The farmer's mother she did bring me out me dinner tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 What other sorts of odd jobs did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Well that's all I could do, on }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1909464\charrsid7686223 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1909464\charrsid7686223  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
farm, work, doing some at or other. In school days and afterwards. Fact of the matter over there it was nothing else. It was all farms over there see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Had you any pedlars coming round at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Only the gypsies }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1909464\charrsid7686223 \{illegible\}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223  did mostly come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 What sort of things would they sell?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Clothes pegs. Chiefly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Would you have meat often? Or was money rather..?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh we did get a bi
t of meat. Fact of the matter we did, I did catch some rabbits in the wires. Fact of the matter the old farmer bought us a long net as you could fold it up and put it in what we used to call the poachers' pocket. We would go out at night, see, two or thre
e of us. And catch some rabbits. That way, then bring 'em home and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8198308\charrsid7686223 \{illegible\}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223  skin em see and cook em see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 All right that wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Yes. Fact of the matter we had to do some at like that to make ends meet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Had you any butchers meat at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh yes. Yes. If you wanted anything extra, well, in our early days, well we did take short cuts. Either down to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8198308\charrsid7686223 \{}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3942983\charrsid7686223 ILLEGIBLE}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8198308\charrsid7686223 \}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
 or else up to up }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8198308\charrsid7686223 Hawkesbury}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223  come up here to Sodbury across the fields. Never hardly touched the road, only just crossed over.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 It was much faster that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 How old were you when you started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 How far away was the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Two mile. I didn't walk the two mile I always take short cuts across the fields.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh I see. How large was the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
Well now, it was, we got up to 100 of us there. And then there was, the time had come see as we couldn't have no more so lads at Little Sodbury, at the bottom, Little Sodbury, had to come over here to Chipping Sodbury to school. And the top 
of Little Sodbury used to come to Horton. Cos there was one lot come to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Horton{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 and they had nearly as far as I to come to school, as lived up on Sodbury Common, farmer's sons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 How many teachers would there be if there were a hundred children altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Ah, one in a classroom, four all told.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Four. Would you have your mid-day meal at home or would you take sandwiches?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Ah always take our own, yes, \{ILLEGIBLE\}
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 What would you take?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh some bread and cheese. Or some bread an
d butter and jam. Cos I loved that. I could make a meal out of that any time of day. Bread and butter and jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Did your mother make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh ah. And me wife did. Fact of the matter I known her, on ever so many occasions, make a hundred weight of jam a season.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Gosh that's an awful lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 It is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 She made her bread as well I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 At the beginning we did. Mother used to make her own bread. And I had to go down to Wickwar and get the balm for making it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 You ran errands for your mother a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 How much older were your brothers and sisters? A lot older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 About how many years?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 I couldn't say exactly. They be all dead now, I am sorry to say. The last one died about eight year ago
. She was ninety-two. That were the oldest of em. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Quite a gap then wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
Yes, well I'm seventy-two. And if my wife had only lived another two months to the very day we should have been married fifty years. It was Before I got married, the farmer said to \{BLANK\}
 where I was at work, Charlie, Henry's leaving, he's going down to Wickwar to live now along with his daughter. And I can give you the first chance of the cottage. So I took it. And I went down to the wife, or sweetheart as was then
, see and told her and she agreed to it and we got married. And took the cottage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Had you saved up at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 No, nothing. Cause it was all on the hop as you might say. Well both }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13271025\charrsid7686223 
of us }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 had some many what we'd saved up between us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Had you any furniture?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Well we had some. We never had up to date furniture then, nothing like today. Same as I've got now, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13271025\charrsid7686223 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13271025\charrsid7686223  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
isn't all flashy stuff not like some. Long as it is clean and tidy that's near enough for me. I would sooner have a little bit and call it me own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 How did you like school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 All right. Yes. Fact of the matter I been up to school in the morning and lit the fires for the woman as cleaned the school. At 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}Eight o'clock{\*\xmlclose} in the morning. Especially if there was a sharp frost or ice on the pon
d or anything or snow. Make our own sledges and get up to the castle and come down. I used to be a bit of a devil on ice.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 You skated did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Yes. Seeing as I went, when we went up to Wembley the first time the lady that next to me said "Can't y
ou keep your feet quiet" and I said "No, I am down there along with them".
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 What sort of skates did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh only them hob nail boots then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh I see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 And they could do the same - I know I had to pay for it!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 What were your favourite lessons at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Arithmetic. Or history.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Were they strict with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh yes, yes, fair. Give 'em their due, we had to do what we was told. Or else get the cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Were you punished a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Well not a lot. Not like some. And we did have two hours for dinner then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 That was a long time. So when did you come home then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}
{\xmlattrvalue 16}}}Four o'clock{\*\xmlclose}. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 15}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 16}}}Quarter past four{\*\xmlclose} in the summer and 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 16}}}four o'clock{\*\xmlclose} in the winter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 What would you spend your evenings doing? as a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Well I was helping some of 'em on the farm summer nights. Every evening, Saturdays and Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 How about in the winter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh yes and then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Were you? Even after dark?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh yes. Clean the cows out. They as was tied up. With a hurricane lantern.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Were your parents strict with you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Fair, fair. Not like they be today... \{BLANK\} I was always in between nine and ten. Not no later. No. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 9}}}Nine o'clock{\*\xmlclose} as a rule.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Were they Church or Chapel people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Church. Then we did have a short cut to that, that was a mile. Across the fields.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 You went every Sunday did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Yes, mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Your parents went as well did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Yes. And I did help do with the bell ringing. Especially in teenage days. I didn't get paid for it see, I did it just 
for the fund of the thing, as the saying is. And on three or four occasions well we did ring the old year out and the new year in.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 What was Christmas like in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Well at school}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13271025\charrsid7686223  i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13271025\charrsid7686223  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 was all right. We did always have the treat. Down at Hort
on Hall. That was Squire Emmett lived there then and we always had a nice tea and an orange and that and some sweets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Anything special at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 No only at Horton. At Christmas. My dad wouldn't drink, you know. I was never one of they that get off
 on the beer and that. After I got married, that, no, I guess I always had plenty on it at work. Beer or cider. Beer in the summer, see and cider in the winter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Had you any brothers and sisters that started work while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh they was all out in service. And married some on 'em, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Were your brothers away from home as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 It was almost like being an only child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Yes, that it, well it was a blessing it was as it happened. I was the last. Well I did bid
e home and looked after 'em. Do the gardening and that in between whiles, nights when I come home from school. And then mornings I'd go down the farm and get Dad's beer and take it to him where he was at work. And then go on to school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 I see. You helped them a fair bit then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh yes. Same as I'm always saying, I believe in it.? \{BLANK\} You don't pay your debts with money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 How old were you when you started work then, after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Thirteen. Left school on the Friday and started w
ork on the Monday. I went over to Kingswood, near Wootton, first. For a few months. Along will a farmer, and then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 How did you get that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Well he asked me for to come, see. Soon as I left school. And then afterwards I left him and come along t
o his father to work, handy for home you see that was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 I see, it wasn't as far walking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
Oh no. Then that was three shillings a week then. Then his father gave me four shillings a week. Course I had to put in an extra hour or two see then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 What sort of hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh, six to six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Was he a good employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
Oh yes, yes. I could get on with them all right. Bar one of them. It went from five to seven shillings a week. And then from seven to eleven shillings a week. The f
act of the matter this other farmer where I left offered me a chance for to go along with his sister. Mrs. Pryior, down at Rhibley, Yate. I thought}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13271025\charrsid7686223  to meself well, shall I or sha}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 n't I, this a long long way for to bike it. Not only that see I should have been on the meal carts and never know what time you get, down at the meal carts. D}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4012096\charrsid7686223 own at the mill, Koubley mill, f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
or the animals feeding stock. I thought to meself goodness knows what time I shall be home at nights. I don't much worry. Better let that bide a
nd go on with this at eleven bob a week then I had two horses for to look after, then And then for to go and plough and help with the milking in between whiles.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 What sort of farms were the ones round here? Were they mostly arable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh yes, all arable and grass and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 And dairy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Yes. More on the dairy line under the hill see. Sheep and that over the top.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 What sort of crops would you grow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Barley and corn and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Down under the hill see
 it was mostly wheat and oats and beans. Very little barley down under the hill. And on, well I was long with that farmer at Horton, for thirty year well I had to do all the cutting round of the corn. It was all done by horses in those days see Binding on
 top. I mind on one summer I cut round four acres of field and took that and then I was on a cutting round all the rest of the time. With a horse crook. I could go faster with a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4012096\charrsid7686223 hook}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223  crook than what I could with a scythe. I could time meself. I went so many
 yards with a scythe then I had to cut it down then sheaf it up and tie it up and throw it back on the side and I could cut with a hoo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4012096\charrsid7686223 k}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223  crook quicker than what I could cut it with a scythe. Soon as I had me }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4012096\charrsid7686223 sheaf\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
 cut well I only just had to tie em up and throw em back. Well I could do it quicker. I know it was a bit warmer work but I didn't mind about that. And then we had up near 100 acres to cut round that time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 An awful lot!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4012096\charrsid7686223 Ah it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 How many men were there working on it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Er. Three of us beside the farmer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Had you any extra help at harvest time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
Ah, in me younger days, there was when it was all done by hand. Or the biggest part of it done by hand. Because, well before I left school see I used to go and rake back for the 
farmer. One or other of the farmers. Before I would go to school of a morning. Then again soon when I come home again nights I would go and rake back or turn it with a rake, a hand rake. There was no machinery in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 What sort of thing would you be working in after harvest, in the Autumn?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh I would go onto hedging then. Laying hedge and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Prune it out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 And then lay it down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Are there thorn hedges down here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Ah yes. But t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2711116\charrsid7686223 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 is all going to wrack and ruin, there's hard
ly any hedges laid today. Today you see well they've got the machine for to cut the tops off. That was my hobby was laying out, hedging and that for the winter. I would start hedging about November and keep on up til May.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh I didn't realise it went on so long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
Oh yes, yes. You get some old hedges I've found them you've always got to live and learn. You never finish learning. And I got on some of the old hedges here, as grow up here fifteen or twenty year old. See well I didn't cut they out and le
t them stop up til May and then they laid down so much better. We the sap was upsee in the middle of winter see you get the big sticks they break off, before you can get them down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 What other jobs were there in the Winter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Dung hauling and things like that. And spreading of it, all by hand \{ILLEGIBLE\} Horses and dung carts you see \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 in the fields and about six yards apart \{ILLEGIBLE\} and later on see you would go and spread that. Then afterwards 'bout February March time you'd go over th
at with a chain harrow, 2 horses and brush it in. And that's where the best of the grass was see. For mowing. When they came over at Old Sodbury off hand milking onto machine milking, well, it were \{ILLEGIBLE\} or nothing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 How old were you when they started having machine milking
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Well I took the job on in February, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2711116\charrsid7686223 '4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 8,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2711116\charrsid7686223  \{38?\}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
 but we couldn't get the cottage not before November. Then I came over here to live see and then I started on the machine then. And when I was there, about two year and a half
, three or four year afterwards, well some of 'em come round see, cos this farmer he was about the only one around this part of the country see that had the milking machine with the glass. When it come from the cow it 50 down into a glass jar and that was
 
measured and weighed at the same time. And some of 'em come round taking films on it. So I was took on the machine at milking and then on another occasion I was on hand milking. And then on another time I was driving the cows in, into the stall. And on an
other place I was throwing up the dung out the barrel. And my mate he was took driving the tractor in. And then some time after that we had to go down to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2711116\charrsid7686223 \{ILLEGIBLE\}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223  that's the farmer, and my mate, we went down to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2711116\charrsid7686223 \{ILLEGIBLE\}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
 and see the film that was on. So I've been on the radio, on the films, and tele.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh, have you now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Ah, on tele. and we went down to the Club, went down to T.W.W. and watched \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 3 or 4 of us ripples set we went up on the well we was in a seat on our own. Mrs. Evans, that was the Chairman of the Club \{I}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16409413\charrsid7686223 LLEGIBL}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 E\} and the Commentator said How do you come to live so old. Well I he said I smoke twist tobacco. And Mrs. Evans spoke up and said aye have a cup of tea. And I was sat next to her and I said Ah without any m
ilk or sugar in it. \{BLANK\}
 on the film. Little did I think as I was on as well. And me daughter, me eldest daughter, come up here because six weeks after this was shown and she said it has been altered. Well I forgot all about it and went down to the loca
l and wasn't in there very long and \{BLANK\} and his wife come in. She said I just seen you on tele. I forgot all about it!
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Had you any outings at all in your childhood? Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh yes, yes. Two or three, outings at different times down to Weston.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 How old were you when you went to the seaside first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 I was somewhere about eight or nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Who took you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 We was drove over in the wagon, over to Sodbury station, and went down by drain down to Weston. Then we had to
 walk see, to Sunday School, it was right up in the Vicarage over at the top of Horton. Oh yes. Then in later years after I left school they had the Sunday School at the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 They had evening classes as well you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Who organised those?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
Well the schoolmaster. I couldn't say exact how many of us went. I counted seven or eight of us went. And after the schoolmaster left Horton his wife wouldn't stop in Horton cos her oldest daughter died sudden and she was worried about it. So t
hey went down to Churchill to live. So I and my mate, Billington, we cycled into \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 he left Horton at Easter time and we went down to see them at Whitsun. And we was down there at nine o'clock in the morning and had a second breakfast. And on our way down, we went up on the ? \{BLANK\}
 Downs I said to my mate, I said, There's a farm up there. I said, we be getting any and he says let's see if we can get a pint of milk so we did, we went up there and got a pint of milk between us and had a \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 some sandwiches who what we had in our pocket. Then we went on down to Churchill and had our second breakfast. Then we stopped to dinner then I and my mate, and Mr. Williams, we cycled on in, on down to Weston. And then we stopped there and went in the p
ictures down there and then we come got back and into Churchill clock was strictly twelve when we got back and we stopped the night there. And had a look round Sunday and I came back on Sunday evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 How did you get your first bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Well I bought it over at Wickwar. It had punctures but I didn't mind about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh - I had left school. Thirteen or fourteen. When I bought me first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Did you give your mother your wages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh yes Had you any spending money?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
Nothing. Just the same after I got married, I never kept back a penny. When we did go to market see, the farmers always give me a shilling. Market money as they used to say in those days. Oh yes. If there was any fish about, see, in the market, well
 I would bring back some fish or if there wasn't no fish then I would bring back the shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Which market was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Well Either Sodbury Yate or Charfield.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Every week would this be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh no, No. Only occasionally. I didn't like Sodbury 'cos that was, \{ILLEGIBLE\} alright for sheep \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 tied up alongside of the National Bank, \{ILLEGIBLE\} If you wanted to buy anything you would have a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3684052\charrsid7686223  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
look at the cattle beforehand, \{ILLEGIBLE\} just the same with the sheep and pigs and all of it. And I
 can mind a few months after that I took me wife up there. And had a look round and showed her all that. There was so much difference in between the first time as I went there and the third time, much alteration. Side roads. Then we come back down into Gl
oucester and I said we'll have a look round the shops and when we got down all the shops were shut. Half day. So I said, well, we went into a caf\'e9
 and had our dinner and then I said well we can go onto Stroud and have a look round there and darn it was just
 the same down there. And on our way see we had to wait at a level crossing, see, and we missed the bus then at Stroud and we had to wait another couple of hours. So we went into a caf\'e9
 there and had a cup of tea and I said to the waiter "Is there any pictures round here", "Yes", "he said told me where to go" and we went in there. And that was "Oklahoma" and when I hear that record then I know that I have seen that picture.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 How did you first meet your wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3684052\charrsid7686223 Well, it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 was her sister introduced her to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 They lived near did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Yes, I knowed her sister beforehand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 How did you know her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
Well I had seen her down there in the street. And the funny part about it I was going into the Eye Hospital with my mother I had to go into the 
Eye Hospital once in every fortnight cos that eye ain't much good and a woman came out as we knowed and she said "Mr. Stinchcombe, we had a bad job happen last night." "I said "What was that?" \{ILLEGIBLE\}
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Had she worked in service at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh yes. She done, the main of her after leaving school was in service. Farms She went to three different farms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 She was in service when you first knew her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Yes. But That was only daily. Were in those days of war Twelve month afterwards she went out to 
service. Then that wasn't far. That was still in \{ILLEGIBLE\} Then she left there, the fact of the matter the farmer sold up there and went up into Wiltshire to live. Then she went down to \{ILLEGIBLE\}
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Had you known her long before you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Er, near enough three year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 What did your parents think of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Happy about it. Yes. The fact of the matter, my mother died well before we got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 How old was your mother when she died? You mustn't have been very old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Well, she w
as seventy-four or five. Cos In them days see they never had the old age pension, not before they were seventy-two. And I went along with her up to Stinchcombe, for to get her birth certificate. Well Dad, see was in Hankesbury, well that where he was born
, but the Registrar was in Horton Mr. Collins. He would do the registering for births and deaths see in Horton and in Hankesbury. Then when he died we came over here to Sodbury.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Who looked after your father then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 After Mother died, soon after see he went down along with his daughter. \{ILLEGIBLE\}
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 He lived until he was eighty-seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh that was a good age wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Yes. He was a cripple like meself. When I was along with Mr. Batten I met with an accident. With a tractor. I told the y
oung fellow as was driving on it, he had just been amongst some chicken coops, I said to him \{BLANK\} and instead of that he went like that and throwed me off. \{ILLEGIBLE\} because he could see I was down and \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 come across me ankle. One blessing it
 was soft ground at his time and I had to shout them lift them up again. And this was because we were just off to dinner so I hung on and helped them out with the milking and then I said to him "You had better ring the boss up" because he was away from th
e farm \{BLANK\} well I couldn't get out of bed. And I had the doctor? \{BLANK\} put in plaster. So I was in plaster then for, this happened in September, up to Christmas then I had to go and see Doctor \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 and I went in and it was nothing near so bad. \{ILLEGIBLE\} And we got talking about farming and he told me he had a brother who was farming out in Australia. And two days after I was listening to the wireless and the Radio Doctor come on, on about \{
ILLEGIBLE\} and said I've knowed this go back one, two 
or three generations and it's right. Because me grandfather had it as well and his sister married and went out to Australia. And one of her grandsons came over here and see I and the Mrs. twelve month before she died and he had it in both hips. It was war
 wounds in the 1st War.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 And he could walk about as well as you. And he was seventy-one. And it was a near miss}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14703675\charrsid7686223 .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223  I had back in 1913. Well Mum and Dad and me sweetheart as was didn't want me to go. So I \{ILLEGIBLE\} Else I should have been out there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Why did you think of going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Because me aunt asked me to come out there. Help out with the farming see. \{ILLEGIBLE\}
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 What happened when the 1}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \super\insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 st}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223  War started? Were you called up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 No. Well \{ILLEGIBLE\} when I went and had me second medical down at \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 and he said "You'll get called up when all the rest is killed". \{ILLEGIBLE\} When I came home, \{ILLEGIBLE\} "Oh" I said "They are going to call me up when all the rest is killed" and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 How much were your wages when you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Fifteen bob a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 How much did the house cost you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 That was in to it. \{ILLEGIBLE\}
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Had you anything else from the farm? Had you milk or potatoes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Oh I had me milk. And butter was only a shilling a pound. Farmhouse butter. I 
had to churn that. Sixty pound at a time. Made Cheese as well. That was all the go in years gone by, butter making and cheese making. So anybody as lived a bit handy, here cos I know one farmer see, he'd sell milk all the time. Well he did bring it round 
in horses, cart or house? \{ILLEGIBLE\}
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 How did your wife buy her groceries and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
We had one that'd come round happen that was baker and grocer. We did have it all off him. That was Mondays, Wednesdays and Saturdays. That he did come with a horse and cart.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 That was very good wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 
Yes. And all of it was good in them days. Ah. I know in several occasions in the Spring of the year when potatoes was getting scarce we used to have off him as much as fifteen or sixteen quarters of bread a week. For eight of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Had you six children then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 I just want to go over the houses you lived in. I think you told Miss Sloan that you started off in a two up, two down cottage ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 .. belonging to the farmer. That was the farmer your father was employed by?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8593187 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 How many years after you were born did you live there? At what age did you move from there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13439349 S  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15617501\charrsid7686223 When (well?) I was married there.
